Description: Fragment of oval handle to modeate turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine orange-buff.
Curator's comments: Name Glaukias. Several such stamps were drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47). From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.16048.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1026)
